.TH SPIDER 1 "2026-06-13" "Hellhound Spider v13.10" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
spider \- SPA and non-SPA web crawler, endpoint discoverer, and attack-surface mapper
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B spider
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fITARGET\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B spider
crawls a target web application, discovers endpoints, forms, parameters,
JavaScript-embedded routes, archived URLs, and exposed configuration or
admin interfaces, then classifies the discovered attack surface (admin
panels, IDOR candidates, authentication endpoints, file upload endpoints,
legacy/deprecated paths, unauthenticated APIs, and sensitive data sources).
.PP
.B spider
deliberately does not attempt to classify endpoints as SQL injection,
command injection, or SSRF candidates based on parameter names alone.
Such heuristics are unreliable and produce a high rate of false positives;
identifying real injection points is left to the operator and to dedicated
testing tools. The parameter map in the report shows every discovered
parameter per endpoint so this assessment can be made manually.
.PP
It combines passive crawling, robots.txt and sitemap parsing, JavaScript
analysis, headless-browser SPA rendering, certificate-transparency based
subdomain discovery, Wayback Machine history mining, and active probing
(admin panels, sensitive files, GraphQL/OpenAPI introspection, and
user-supplied wordlists) into a single pass, producing a structured JSON
report and a human-readable summary.
.PP
\fITARGET\fR is the base URL of the application to scan, e.g.
.IR https://example.com .
.SH OPTIONS
.SS "Scan Options"
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-depth " " \fIN\fR
Maximum crawl depth (default: 4).
.TP
.BR \-W ", " \-\-delay " " \fIS\fR
Fixed delay between requests per host, in seconds (default: 0, adaptive).
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-concurrency " " \fIN\fR
Number of concurrent crawl workers (default: 12).
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-timeout " " \fIS\fR
Per-request timeout in seconds (default: 15).
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Show all discovery logs, including low-confidence and informational events.
.SS "Authentication"
.TP
.BR \-C ", " \-\-cookie " " \fICOOKIE\fR
Cookie string, dict-style string, or path to a cookie file. Used to scan
authenticated areas of the application.
.TP
.BR \-a ", " \-\-auth " " \fIHEADER\fR
Authorization header value, e.g. \fB"Bearer eyJ..."\fR.
.TP
.BR \-u ", " \-\-basic\-auth " " \fIUSER:PASS\fR
HTTP Basic authentication credentials, curl-style, e.g.
\fBadmin:password\fR.
.SS "Output"
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-out " " \fIFILE\fR
Write an additional copy of the report to \fIFILE\fR. A JSON report is
always saved automatically regardless of this option.
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-format " " "{json,jsonl,csv,burp,urls,nuclei}"
Extra output format for the report written to \fB\-\-out\fR
(default: \fBjson\fR).
.SS "Feature Flags"
.TP
.BR \-P ", " \-\-no\-playwright
Disable headless browser SPA scanning. Without this flag, \fBspider\fR
attempts patchright, then playwright-stealth, then falls back to manual
JavaScript analysis.
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-no\-probing
Disable the intelligent active-probing phase (admin panels, sensitive
files, GraphQL, OpenAPI).
.TP
.BR \-I ", " \-\-spa\-interact
Enable SPA form filling and button clicking during headless browser
scanning. Only use against targets you are authorized to test, as this
performs active interactions with the application.
.TP
.BR \-R ", " \-\-no\-cors
Disable CORS misconfiguration checks.
.TP
.BR \-G ", " \-\-no\-graphql
Disable GraphQL introspection probing.
.TP
.BR \-O ", " \-\-no\-openapi
Disable OpenAPI / Swagger discovery.
.TP
.BR \-x ", " \-\-extract
Enable passive data extraction of emails, IP addresses, and cloud storage
bucket references found in crawled content.
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-screenshot " " [\fIPRESET\fR]
Capture screenshots of key endpoints. \fIPRESET\fR may be one of:
\fBall\fR, \fBstandard\fR, \fBblocked\fR, \fBerrors\fR, \fBapi\fR,
\fBadmin\fR, or a regular expression matching endpoint URLs. Defaults to
\fBstandard\fR if no preset is given.
.TP
.BR \-F ", " \-\-no\-filter
Disable the noise-path filter, including VCS browser UI paths, CDN asset
paths, and socket.io endpoints in the output.
.TP
.BR \-N ", " \-\-no\-crawl
Skip BFS link crawling entirely. Only the recon and probe modules run:
robots.txt and sitemap parsing, admin panel probing, sensitive file
probing, wordlist-based discovery (\fB\-\-wordlist\fR), subdomain
enumeration (\fB\-\-subdomains\fR), and Wayback Machine history mining.
Useful for fast, targeted reconnaissance without traversing the site's
link graph.
.SS "Scope"
.TP
.BR \-\-subdomains
Enable subdomain enumeration via certificate transparency logs.
.TP
.BR \-S ", " \-\-follow\-subdomains
Crawl discovered subdomains within the base domain.
.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-follow\-redirects
Follow cross-host redirects and add the destination host to scope.
.TP
.BR \-\-scope " " \fIHOSTS\fR
Comma-separated list of additional hosts to include in scope, e.g.
\fBapi.target.com,cdn.target.com\fR.
.TP
.BR \-\-wordlist " " \fIFILE\fR
Path to a newline-separated wordlist of directory and file names. Each
entry is requested against the target; responses are filtered through the
same soft-404 and canary-fingerprint logic used for sensitive-file
detection, so only meaningful hits are reported. Combine with
\fB\-\-no\-crawl\fR for a discovery-only pass.
.SS "Utilities"
.TP
.BR \-D ", " \-\-diff " " \fIOLD_REPORT\fR
Diff the results of this scan against a previous JSON report, highlighting
new, removed, and changed endpoints.
.TP
.BR \-H ", " \-\-har " " \fIHAR_FILE\fR
Import a browser HAR session file to seed the scan with authenticated or
otherwise hard-to-reach requests captured during manual browsing.
.TP
.BR \-\-upgrade
Upgrade \fBspider\fR to the latest version.
.SS "General"
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show a summary of command-line options and exit.
.SH OUTPUT
.B spider
always writes a JSON report to the working directory, named after the
target host and scan timestamp. The on-screen summary includes:
.PP
.RS
.IP \(bu 3
response headers and missing security headers
.IP \(bu 3
TLS/certificate findings
.IP \(bu 3
detected technology stack
.IP \(bu 3
robots.txt disallowed paths and discovered endpoints
.IP \(bu 3
a parameter map of query, form, and runtime parameters per endpoint
.IP \(bu 3
authentication-walled endpoints
.IP \(bu 3
intelligence classifications: admin panels, IDOR candidates, file upload
endpoints, authentication endpoints, unauthenticated APIs, sensitive data
sources, and legacy/deprecated endpoints
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Scan a target with default settings:
.B spider http://target.example
.TP
Authenticated scan using a session cookie:
.B spider \-C "PHPSESSID=abc123" http://target.example
.TP
Recon-only pass with a custom wordlist, no link crawling:
.B spider \-N \-\-wordlist ~/wordlists/common.txt http://target.example
.TP
Full reconnaissance including subdomain enumeration, no crawl:
.B spider \-N \-\-subdomains \-\-wordlist ~/wordlists/common.txt http://target.example
.TP
SPA scan with headless browser interaction enabled:
.B spider \-I https://app.example
.TP
Import a HAR capture and diff against a previous report:
.B spider \-H session.har \-D previous_report.json http://target.example
.SH FILES
.TP
.I spider_<host>_<timestamp>.json
Auto-saved JSON report for each scan.
